OL,6,F"(The tax) puts an unfair tax burden
OL,7,Fon low income households - and
OL,8,Fproperty values are already more than
OL,9,F20 years out of date", said Assistant
OL,10,FDirector Luke Young. We do not see a
OL,11,Fclear benefit for the people we
OL,12,Fsupport in waiting until 2028 to begin
OL,13,Fthe revaluation.J"In recent months we
OL,14,Fhave seen a worrying rise in the
OL,15,Fnumber of people struggling with
OL,16,Fcouncil tax arrears. In the first
OL,17,Fmonths of 2024, we saw 19% more people
OL,18,Fwith council tax debt compared to the
OL,19,Fsame time last year.J"Having pushed
OL,20,Fback wider reform the Welsh Government
OL,21,Fnow need, as a bare minimum, to get on
OL,22,Fwith essential action to stop the poor
OL,23,Fdebt collection practices that make
OL,24,Fthings worse for people. We also want
OL,25,Fto see quick progress to simplify
OL,26,Faccess to Council Tax Reduction for
